-- Hugo Boss posts rise in 2006 net income
-- 
-- Wed Jan 31, 2007 5:24am EST
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2007/01/31/us-hugoboss-idUSWEB166920070131

 

 FRANKFURT  (Reuters) - German fashion firm Hugo Boss BOSG_p.DE on Wednesday posted a 19 percent rise in 2006 net income. 


 The upmarket suit maker, which is controlled by Italy's Valentino V.MI, said in a statement net income came in at 129 million euros ($167.2 million). Sales rose by 14 percent to 1.496 billion euros last year, while pretax profit rose 14 percent to 180 million euros. For 2007, Hugo Boss said the positive earnings and sales trend would continue.